The paper deals with the computational complexity of model checking computation tree logic (CTL) over one-counter processes (OCPs), which are pushdown processes. This topic falls under the area of formal methods and verification, which is typically categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also involves analyzing the periodic behavior of CTL over OCPs, which could potentially fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper uses results from complexity theory, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages).
